      • CHILD_ENTRY_KEY

        public static final String CHILD_ENTRY_KEY
        Converters will populate metadatata. If the entry is an object or a file, its name will reflect that. Interpreting the entry name as a file name on a file system is up to the recipient. E.g., Mail attachments might be file names; Embedded objects may be object IDs.

      • is_RFC822_attachment

        public boolean is_RFC822_attachment
        Mail messages are ridiculous complex compound documents. The parent document and all its attachments are marked as is_RFC822_attachment = true. HTML and text formats are most susceptible to encoding issues.

      • evalParentContainer

        @Deprecated
public void evalParentContainer​(boolean saveEmbedded)
        Deprecated. -- prefer to have children archived with originals always. If you are pulling off binary data from originals (email, compound docs, etc) you will go nuts tracking it all.
        If this doc is a Parent doc, then evaluate what its "container" should be, that is to house child objects and their conversions. If it is a child, ignore -- ensure child.parentContainer = child.parent.parentContainer Children do not get to choose.
        Parameters:
        saveEmbedded - if embedded children should be saved to disk

      • evalParentChildContainer

        public void evalParentChildContainer​()
        Evaluate a folder for archiving children close to where the parent original resides. Whereas evalParentContainer(boolean) which tries to choose if children are archived embedded with parents in ./xtext or in a parallel archive.

      • hasText

        public boolean hasText​()
        Reports if the doc has text available, after it was converted. NOTE: this is false if you ask before it is converted.
        Returns:
        true if there is text available. false if the converters have not tried to set text or they tried and found no text.

      • setDefaultID

        public void setDefaultID​()
                  throws IOException,
                         NoSuchAlgorithmException
        Set default ID only after all conversion and all metadata has been acquired. MD5 hash of text, if text is available, or of the filepath if file is empty.
        Throws:
        IOException - on err
        NoSuchAlgorithmException - on err

      • setPathRelativeTo

        public void setPathRelativeTo​(String container,
                              boolean childrenWithParent)
        Find the relative path where this item should reside. 
           Given file  /source/a/b/c.xyz
   where will reside in archive?    /archive/.../source/a/b/c.xyz
        Parent/Child relationship is complicated still.
        Parameters:
        container - folder that represents the parent document
        childrenWithParent - true if you want to save child near parent.

      • _saveConversion

        protected void _saveConversion​(File target)

        Internal function for saving buffer in the XText format. IF the converted original file as a date/time later than that of the cached conversion, this conversion cache will be overwritten.

      • saveBuffer

        public void saveBuffer​(File target)
                throws IOException
        Internally save Buffer with its metadata to a given filepath Expert mode: use this only if you know what you are doing. You can add additional metadata to the meta sheet using addProperty() Then overwrite existing doc conversions
        Parameters:
        target - cached file to save a conversion.
        Throws:
        IOException - on error saving content
